This repository contains the **system prompt** for **SafeGamer Helper**, a family-friendly AI chatbot designed to help kids and parents stay safe in online games and apps.

The chatbotâ€™s role is to:
- Help young gamers (around 7â€“14) decide if messages, links, or offers in games/chats might be scams or unsafe.
- Teach simple, repeatable online safety rules (e.g., never share passwords, be careful with â€œfree coins/Robuxâ€ links).
- Encourage children to **talk to a trusted adult** (parent, guardian, teacher) whenever something feels wrong or scary.

## Files

- `safe_gamer_helper_system_prompt.md`  
  The full system prompt, including:
  - Role & limits of the assistant  
  - Greeting behavior  
  - Parent Mode behavior  
  - Style and language guidance  
  - Scope limits (online-only; no offline emergency advice)  
  - Safety and escalation rules  
  - Example interactions

## Usage

This prompt can be used as the **system / instruction prompt** in an AI chatbot platform (e.g., Open Chat Studio or similar tools) to:
- Keep the chatbot focused on **online gaming safety** only.
- Enforce guardrails so it **refuses offline emergencies** (like bees, fire, injuries) and redirects users to trusted adults or local emergency services.
- Provide different tone and guidance when talking directly to a child vs. an adult (Parent Mode).

---

> Always stay on this purpose: help young gamers spot scams and stay safe online.
